        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b> Disclosure; and Encouragement of Verification, Innovation, Cleaning, and Efficiency Act of 2021 or the DEVICE Act of 2021 </b></p> <p>This bill addresses design changes and reprocessing of medical devices. </p> <p>Specifically, medical device manufacturers must notify the Food and Drug Administration (1) before making changes to the design or reprocessing instructions of a device, and (2) no more than five days after widely disseminating to health care providers in a foreign country communications regarding changes to the design or reprocessing instructions of a device or regarding a safety concern about a device. (Reprocessing of medical devices is the process for cleaning and sterilizing or disinfecting devices for reuse.) </p> <p>A device may not be sold if the manufacturer violates these notification requirements.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
